   3.813225540628809*^9},ExpressionUUID->"72202a90-000c-664c-9b27-\
295d5a9b376d"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Note that the total potential energy for the nuclear positions within the \
Born-Oppenheimer approximation is given by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox[
   StyleBox["E",
    FontSlant->"Italic"], 
   StyleBox["e",
    FontSlant->"Italic"]]],ExpressionUUID->
  "23a128b9-109f-4bfc-8de9-63a48a8b3349"],
 ". For polyatomic molecules, this function gives a multidimensional \
potential energy surface like that shown in Figure 10.2, where each degree of \
freedom of the molecule represents one of the dimensions of the surface."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132242114679546`*^9, 3.8132242455496116`*^9}, {
  3.813225561870835*^9, 3.8132255631330338`*^9}, {3.91950370775694*^9, 
  3.9195037194453163`*^9}, {3.9374864666296215`*^9, 
  3.937486466929514*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1cfbaa86-c76f-483b-9783-\
f0096d641072"],

