Cell[TextData[{
 "The first term contains the Hamiltonian operator of an isolated hydrogen \
atom with the electron in the 1",
 StyleBox["s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " orbital, which yields the energy of an electron in a 1",
 StyleBox["s",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " orbital of hydrogen when it acts on the wavefunction ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
   RowBox[{"1", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["s",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["A",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.919505649948021*^9, 3.9195056602880173`*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"e0b436ad-b66e-44fb-a6ef-fd9819310b00"],
 ".The second term represents the energetic contribution from the attractive \
interaction between an electron in the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
   RowBox[{"1", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["s",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["A",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]]}]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.8132221669142685`*^9, 3.8132221794693403`*^9}, {
    3.8132222690385857`*^9, 3.813222292552426*^9}, {3.8132225103046436`*^9, 
    3.8132225357976294`*^9}, 3.813225530724597*^9, {3.8132268996594105`*^9, 
    3.8132268997936573`*^9}, {3.8132269718506794`*^9, 
    3.8132270598936987`*^9}, {3.813227090063882*^9, 3.8132270928942423`*^9}, {
    3.8132273687054873`*^9, 3.8132273956726027`*^9}, {3.8132274257354927`*^9, 
    3.8132274504676456`*^9}, {3.813227484968296*^9, 3.8132274916733313`*^9}, {
    3.813227717592659*^9, 3.813227799104663*^9}, {3.8132278524338465`*^9, 
    3.813227854764579*^9}, 3.8132279269606223`*^9, {3.8132284806854115`*^9, 
    3.8132285040063257`*^9}, {3.813233670328187*^9, 3.8132336720975046`*^9}, {
    3.8132357631856723`*^9, 3.8132357709170113`*^9}, {3.813427542982295*^9, 
    3.8134276318539715`*^9}, {3.8134276920016794`*^9, 
    3.8134278213405004`*^9}, {3.8134283865881367`*^9, 3.813428403776387*^9}, {
    3.8134286895668926`*^9, 3.8134287345464907`*^9}, {3.8134287799089575`*^9, 
    3.813428844637398*^9}, {3.8134289130960608`*^9, 3.8134289167162104`*^9}, {
    3.81349259000589*^9, 3.8134925953896093`*^9}, {3.813501462614107*^9, 
    3.813501486415373*^9}, {3.8135015276868563`*^9, 3.813501543482114*^9}},
  ExpressionUUID->"0a7baa99-54e8-2b4c-96d0-091bb1ef5f04"],
 " orbital with nucleus ",
 StyleBox["B",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". Sometimes, this second term is called a coulomb integral, but that \
conflicts with a definition of the coulomb integral for interaction between \
electrons (not between nuclei and electrons). We will therefore call this the \
attractive potential term ",
 StyleBox["N",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and we write "
}], "Text",
