Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 10.6",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Plot of the bonding molecular orbital for hydrogen. The top graph shows a \
contour plot of the wavefunction in two dimensions, and the bottom graph \
shows the corresponding one-dimensional plot along the internuclear axis. The \
internuclear distance can be varied using the bar at the top. M. G. Raymer \
(June 2011) , Wolfram Demonstrations, CC BY-NC-SA 3.0, \
https://demonstrations.wolfram.com/\
LCAOApproximationToBondingMolecularOrbitalInHydrogen/."
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
   3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
   3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.809510876137825*^9, 3.809510907739876*^9}, {
   3.809968073566992*^9, 3.8099681536568317`*^9}, {3.810557260250428*^9, 
   3.8105572606139913`*^9}, {3.8130835305386977`*^9, 
   3.8130836194514275`*^9}, {3.813224407772764*^9, 3.8132244817756805`*^9}, {
   3.8132354037950773`*^9, 3.813235501614183*^9}, 3.813236418234542*^9, {
   3.81351439000795*^9, 3.8135143988971663`*^9}, {3.813665905470446*^9, 
   3.8136660007466154`*^9}, {3.8136660571324577`*^9, 3.81366605723772*^9}, {
   3.8136663097257414`*^9, 3.8136664742951727`*^9}, {3.9195126299125423`*^9, 
   3.919512630310216*^9}, {3.9374875752846184`*^9, 
   3.937487575569187*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"44634006-07f7-419d-a8c8-\
fbee5db76f83"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Molecular Orbitals of Multielectron Molecules", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8136665793928785`*^9, 3.8136665880390153`*^9}, {
  3.813666698635479*^9, 
  3.8136666995614643`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"84fc756e-2554-4569-bf67-\
f3b8ebd109d9"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[{
 "MO Description of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["H",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a9dd706e-2f01-465a-87bc-0680bca4b139"]
}], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813666591241805*^9, 
  3.8136666272630043`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"d2c9c5d6-490a-403f-b68a-\
79125668009b"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We have now described in detail the molecular orbitals of the \
single-electron diatomic ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox[
    StyleBox["H",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2", "+"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d33025bd-8120-4a50-8dc3-f9228fe117ee"],
 ", but we have not addressed the issue of how we then tackle a multielectron \
molecule. You might be familiar with the concept of filling MO energy \
diagrams according to the Pauli exclusion and Aufbau principles, but where do \
these ideas come from? How would we write the wavefunction of such a system?"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813666641473254*^9, 3.813666792290657*^9}, {
   3.813670523493564*^9, 3.8136705259134803`*^9}, 3.813684610748551*^9, {
   3.9196715147677975`*^9, 
   3.9196715159929967`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"47d87a47-15bf-42ea-ba9b-\
40310f6c18fd"],

Cell["\<\
It turns out that this question is not as challenging to address as it might \
seem; we can employ the same approach that we built up for describing \
multielectron atoms. In that case, we described each atomic orbital as a \
linear combination of hydrogen-like atomic orbitals (or, in practice, \
Slater-type orbitals or Gaussian-type orbitals),\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813670530876745*^9, 3.813670571287774*^9}, {
   3.813670622253086*^9, 3.813670696603383*^9}, {3.813672251599329*^9, 
   3.813672267617513*^9}, 
   3.937577203218008*^9},ExpressionUUID->"bbc3528d-ce0f-c04c-804e-\
a86e6394d5cc"],

Cell[BoxData[
 RowBox[{
  RowBox[{
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", 
    StyleBox["i",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{"(", 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["r",
      FontWeight->"Bold",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], ")"}]}], "=", 
  RowBox[{
   UnderscriptBox["\[Sum]", 
    StyleBox["p",
     FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["C",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], 
     StyleBox["pi",
      FontSlant->"Italic"]], 
    SubscriptBox[
     StyleBox["f",
      FontSlant->"Italic"], "p"], 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     SubscriptBox[
      StyleBox["r",
       FontWeight->"Bold",
       FontSlant->"Italic"], "1"], ")"}]}]}]}]], "DisplayFormulaNumbered",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.810112811439228*^9, 3.8101128248442793`*^9}, {
