   3.813233662702242*^9}, {3.813676741631068*^9, 
   3.813676829221445*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5bf2fdfb-1826-4a68-a540-\
9a787fd16a08"],

Cell["\<\
which will generate additional molecular orbitals as solutions to the \
electronic Hamiltonian.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813676856652149*^9, 
  3.8136768924923086`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"683fddef-b7ee-425b-b3dc-\
b8e94b1eabd4"],

Cell["\<\
This process yields the molecular orbitals that you are likely familiar with \
from general chemistry courses. Specifically, the energies of these molecular \
orbitals are typically displayed in a molecular orbital energy diagram, with \
the constituent atom orbital energies on the left and right side and the \
molecular orbital energies in the center. An interactive module displaying \
such energy diagrams for the first- and second-row diatomic molecules is \
shown in Figure 10.7.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.813676905536302*^9, 3.813677035197181*^9}, {
  3.919671781157131*^9, 3.9196717815192347`*^9}, {3.9374876917090244`*^9, 
  3.937487692325691*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"295356f6-a505-43a4-a24d-\
a74305844c1f"],

