Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 10.13",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". Internuclear potential energy curves of the ground state and excited \
states of ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox[
    StyleBox["H",
     FontSlant->"Plain"], "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "99f90a3d-f080-465c-93a8-0bb077feb23c"],
 ". Lee, Chun-Woo, Gim, Yeongrok, & Choi, Tae Hoon. (2013). Calculation of \
Potential Energy Curves of Excited States of Molecular Hydrogen by \
Multi-Reference Configuration-interaction Method. Bulletin of the Korean \
Chemical Society, ",
 StyleBox["34",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "(6), 1771\[Dash]1778. https://doi.org/10.5012/bkcs.2013.34.6.1771"
}], "Affiliation",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.809435027311596*^9, 3.8094350763900714`*^9}, {
   3.80943583474421*^9, 3.8094358359299717`*^9}, {3.8094472165104203`*^9, 
   3.809447281165168*^9}, {3.809510876137825*^9, 3.809510907739876*^9}, {
   3.809968073566992*^9, 3.8099681536568317`*^9}, {3.810557260250428*^9, 
   3.8105572606139913`*^9}, {3.8130835305386977`*^9, 
   3.8130836194514275`*^9}, {3.813224407772764*^9, 3.8132244817756805`*^9}, {
   3.814107987969291*^9, 3.814108049630145*^9}, {3.814109089245699*^9, 
   3.8141091270231557`*^9}, {3.8141093100266285`*^9, 3.814109310147791*^9}, {
   3.814109921841116*^9, 3.8141099219695177`*^9}, {3.8141099776142817`*^9, 
   3.8141100720635233`*^9}, {3.814117676987705*^9, 3.8141177066264424`*^9}, {
   3.9196744971818137`*^9, 3.9196745206434407`*^9}, 3.9196745798446255`*^9, {
   3.9374880921596375`*^9, 
   3.937488093716278*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3cd492d9-0f43-432a-b8b3-\
8547a68b5f0f"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "One final note about molecular term symbols: often a slightly different, \
empirical notation is employed. In this notation, the ground state is given \
the term symbol ",
 StyleBox["X",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", and excited states with the same multiplicity are given the labels of ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["B",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["C",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", etc. in increasing order of energy. States with a different multiplicity \
are given the labels of ",
 StyleBox["a",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["b",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", ",
 StyleBox["c",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", etc. In the case of polyatomic molecules, these symbols can also appear \
with a tilde (e.g. ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["X", "~"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ba50d8ce-6356-4c2f-b897-b8468cdd3efa"],
 "). You may encounter such terminology, for example, in a paper that \
examines the ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "\[RightArrow]",
 StyleBox["X",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " transition (photoemission from the first excited state) of a molecule. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8141177712979794`*^9, 3.814117943803562*^9}, {
  3.814117986932828*^9, 
  3.8141179901695013`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a32e2bdd-15bd-40a4-98cd-\
1cd93bad170e"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]]
